[5] Diarrhea, fatal - Cameroon
Date: Fri, 12 Nov 2004
From: Promed-Port@promedmail.org
Source: Panapress 10 Nov 2004 [in Portuguese, summarized & edited by Mod.JW]
<http://www.panapress.com>

3 people have died since mid October 2004 in Zingui (south), Cameroon, West
Africa, from a strange diarrhea, according to the independent daily
"Mutations" in its Wed 10 Nov 2004 edition. 10 similar cases are currently
under observation by the health services, according to the same source.
Symptoms are diarrhea and bloody vomit, swollen feet, edema, fatigue,
malaise, and hearing problems. The local people ascribe it to witchcraft or
Ebola and are treating it with tree bark [infusions], but health
authorities attribute it to amebic or bacterial dysentery caused by
drinking dirty water. [The clinical picture suggests shigellosis or
salmonellosis, or possibly campylobacter or yersinia infection. ï¿½ Mod.LJS]
